{"translation":{"id":"BSB","name":"Berean Standard Bible","website":"https://berean.bible/","licenseUrl":"https://berean.bible/","licenseNotes":null,"shortName":"BSB","englishName":"Berean Standard Bible","language":"eng","textDirection":"ltr","sha256":"b2898c49cadb50fd8763feb9e2f74a90a3817e33408a24b6cbf09e7a950dde97","availableFormats":["json"],"listOfBooksApiLink":"/api/BSB/books.json","numberOfBooks":66,"totalNumberOfChapters":1189,"totalNumberOfVerses":31086,"languageName":"English","languageEnglishName":"English"},"book":{"id":"ECC","translationId":"BSB","name":"Ecclesiastes","commonName":"Ecclesiastes","title":"Ecclesiastes","order":21,"numberOfChapters":12,"sha256":"32e02f44d73846438a7576f1fdd942d7d85382c2e907c9084c49dc1dedc25e37","firstChapterNumber":1,"firstChapterApiLink":"/api/BSB/ECC/1.json","lastChapterNumber":12,"lastChapterApiLink":"/api/BSB/ECC/12.json","totalNumberOfVerses":222},"chapter":{"number":1,"content":[{"type":"heading","content":["Everything Is Futile"]},{"type":"verse","number":1,"content":["These are the words of the Teacher,",{"noteId":0},"the son of David, king in Jerusalem:"]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":2,"content":[{"text":"“Futility","poem":1},{"noteId":1},{"text":"of futilities,”","poem":1},{"text":"says the Teacher,","poem":2},{"text":"“futility of futilities!","poem":1},{"text":"Everything is futile!”","poem":2}]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":3,"content":[{"text":"What does a man gain from all his labor,","poem":1},{"text":"at which he toils under the sun?","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":4,"content":[{"text":"Generations come and generations go,","poem":1},{"text":"but the earth remains forever.","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":5,"content":[{"text":"The sun rises and the sun sets;","poem":1},{"text":"it hurries back to where it rises.","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":6,"content":[{"text":"The wind blows southward,","poem":1},{"text":"then turns northward;","poem":2},{"text":"round and round it swirls,","poem":1},{"text":"ever returning on its course.","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":7,"content":[{"text":"All the rivers flow into the sea,","poem":1},{"text":"yet the sea is never full;","poem":2},{"text":"to the place from which the streams come,","poem":1},{"text":"there again they flow.","poem":2}]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":8,"content":[{"text":"All things are wearisome,","poem":1},{"text":"more than one can describe;","poem":2},{"text":"the eye is not satisfied with seeing,","poem":1},{"text":"nor the ear content with hearing.","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":9,"content":[{"text":"What has been will be again,","poem":1},{"text":"and what has been done will be done again;","poem":2},{"lineBreak":true},{"text":"there is nothing new under the sun.","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":10,"content":[{"text":"Is there a case where one can say,","poem":1},{"text":"“Look, this is new”?","poem":2},{"text":"It has already existed","poem":1},{"text":"in the ages before us.","poem":2}]},{"type":"verse","number":11,"content":[{"text":"There is no remembrance","poem":1},{"text":"of those who came before,","poem":2},{"text":"and those yet to come will not be remembered","poem":1},{"text":"by those who follow after.","poem":2}]},{"type":"heading","content":["With Wisdom Comes Sorrow"]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":12,"content":["I, the Teacher, was king over Israel in Jerusalem."]},{"type":"verse","number":13,"content":["And I set my mind to seek and explore by wisdom all that is done under heaven. What a heavy burden God has laid upon the sons of men to occupy them!"]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":14,"content":["I have seen all the things that are done under the sun, and have found them all to be futile, a pursuit of the wind."]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":15,"content":[{"text":"What is crooked cannot be straightened,","poem":1},{"text":"and what is lacking cannot be counted.","poem":2}]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":16,"content":["I said to myself, “Behold, I have grown and increased in wisdom beyond all those before me who were over Jerusalem, and my mind has observed a wealth of wisdom and knowledge.”"]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":17,"content":["So I set my mind to know wisdom and madness and folly; I learned that this, too, is a pursuit of the wind."]},{"type":"line_break"},{"type":"verse","number":18,"content":[{"text":"For with much wisdom comes much sorrow,","poem":1},{"text":"and as knowledge grows, grief increases.","poem":2}]}],"footnotes":[{"noteId":0,"caller":"+","text":"Or the Convener or the Preacher or the leader of the assembly; Hebrew Qoheleth is rendered as the Teacher throughout Ecclesiastes.","reference":{"chapter":1,"verse":1}},{"noteId":1,"caller":"+","text":"Literally vapor or breath; the Hebrew words translated in Ecclesiastes as forms of futile or fleeting can also be translated as vanity or meaningless.","reference":{"chapter":1,"verse":2}}]},"thisChapterLink":"/api/BSB/ECC/1.json","thisChapterAudioLinks":{"gilbert":"https://openbible.com/audio/gilbert/BSB_21_Ecc_001_G.mp3","hays":"https://openbible.com/audio/hays/BSB_21_Ecc_001_H.mp3","souer":"https://openbible.com/audio/souer/BSB_21_Ecc_001.mp3"},"nextChapterApiLink":"/api/BSB/ECC/2.json","nextChapterAudioLinks":{"gilbert":"https://openbible.com/audio/gilbert/BSB_21_Ecc_002_G.mp3","hays":"https://openbible.com/audio/hays/BSB_21_Ecc_002_H.mp3","souer":"https://openbible.com/audio/souer/BSB_21_Ecc_002.mp3"},"previousChapterApiLink":"/api/BSB/PRO/31.json","previousChapterAudioLinks":{"gilbert":"https://openbible.com/audio/gilbert/BSB_20_Pro_031_G.mp3","hays":"https://openbible.com/audio/hays/BSB_20_Pro_031_H.mp3","souer":"https://openbible.com/audio/souer/BSB_20_Pro_031.mp3"},"numberOfVerses":18}